The @cite{@value{PACKAGE_TITLE}} package is an implementation of the Internet Protocol suite for
@cite{Linux Fast-STREAMS} directly over Linux NET4 Sockets implementation, using a @dfn{STREAMS}
over @dfn{Sockets} approach.  This permits modules to be pushed on UDP or TCP Streams and allows use
of the XTI/TLI library with Internet Protocols on Linux.  The package now also includes direct
@dfn{STREAMS} implementations of RAW IP and UDP, and will include direct implementations of TI
loopback devices and TCP in the future.

This @cite{OpenSS7 Project} release is another separate add-on package release of the
@cite{@value{PACKAGE_TITLE}} package that was formerly present in the (now deprecated) @cite{LiS}
package.  The networking drivers are provided, as well as the TPI and XTI header files for INET
and loopback operation.  The package contains all the necessary manual pakges and other
documentation for INET components in a spearate autoconf tarball.
This release is a stable, production grade release for @cite{Linux Fast-STREAMS} and is part of the
OpenSS7 Master Package (@file{openss7-@value{VERSION_OPENSS7}}).

@ignore
The @cite{@value{PACKAGE_TITLE}} package contains header files and a number of modules and drivers
and the associated documentation that were formerly contained in the @cite{OpenSS7 Linux STREAMS
(LiS)} releases.  When development started on @cite{Linux Fast-STREAMS} in 2003, these modules were
removed from the @cite{LiS} distribution and separated so that they could build against both the
@cite{LiS} and @cite{Linux Fast-STREAMS} packages from the same baseline code.

@end ignore
